				"speakerSlotDescription": [
					{}
				],
				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "Minsc at a party organized by Withers.\r\nVariants:\r\nMinsc's allied with Nine-Fingers state: The player convinced Minsc to see the nuance between good and evil and set aside his differences with the Guild to work with them. His version of this is being a corrective measure to them - he has dragged a Guild thief along to the party with him so he can observe 'real' heroes.\r\n\r\nMinsc base state: The player failed / didn't try to convince Minsc of this nuance, so he's back to his usual ways - getting way in over his head by utterly refusing to compromise. In this case, Withers portal found him while he was imprisoned in a Zhentarim stronghold awaiting execution. But he's not phased, because Minsc believes he can survive anything (and in this case, he probably can by sheer force of optimism/brute violence.)"
				}
			}
		}
